In this article, it is stated that President Obama called Prime Minister John Key of New Zealand to express his condolences for the devastating earthquake that hit Christchurch on February 22, 2011. The President mentioned that a U.S. search and rescue team was on its way to New Zealand and offered further assistance if needed. He also emphasized the strong friendship between the American and New Zealand people. Prime Minister Key acknowledged the determination of the people of Christchurch and thanked the U.S. for their support.